        <abstract> 
<p>SB’s book [<hi rend="italic">Life and habit</hi> (1878)] will be bound shortly. He will send two copies, one of which can be given to CD. To SB’s surprise it has turned out to be an attack on CD’s views and a defence of Lamarck; describes how he was brought to the opinions expressed in it.</p> 
        </abstract>
